7.1.3 - M365SR01: Non-Compliance with M365 Hardening Blueprints
ISM controls:
•	Control: 1560; Revision: 3; Updated: Dec-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Configuration of cloud services)
•	Control: 1506; Revision: 1; Updated: Jun-21; Applicability: All; OS: All (Evaluation of cloud service security)
•	Control: 1564; Revision: 0; Updated: Sep-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Securing cloud service administration)
________________________________________
Current Risk
Insufficient, incomplete implementation or deviation from the ASD and Microsoft System Hardening Blueprint controls for core M365 services (Entra ID, Microsoft 365, Intune, Defender, Purview, Teams as well as Exchange and SharePoint Online), resulting in the compromise of confidentiality, availability and integrity of agency systems, data and/or information.
Risk Assessment:
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
ALMOST CERTAIN	x	MAJOR	=	EXTREME
________________________________________
Recommendations:
1.	Adopt Secure Configuration Baselines: Formally implement the ASD Microsoft 365 Blueprint and Microsoft’s best-practice security baselines across all active M365 services.
2.	Continuous Compliance Monitoring: Utilize Microsoft Purview and Microsoft Defender for Cloud to provide real-time visibility into the tenant's security posture and drift from the hardening baseline.
3.	Establish Configuration Governance: Implement a robust change management process that requires security impact assessments for any modifications to the core M365 security architecture.
- Treatment #1
•	Baseline Alignment Audit: Perform a comprehensive gap analysis of the current M365 configuration against the ASD System Hardening Blueprint to identify and prioritize remediation of non-compliant settings.
•	Technical Enforcement: Use Intune configuration profiles and Entra ID Conditional Access policies to programmatically enforce hardening controls across the identity and device planes.
•	Automated Posture Alerts: Configure automated alerts within the Microsoft 365 Security Centre to notify administrators immediately when critical security settings are altered.
________________________________________
Residual risk outcome if recommendation is implemented.
Implementing a systematic hardening framework ensures that core services are protected by industry-standard defenses, closing common security gaps. While a sophisticated adversary may still attempt to target the platform, the reduction in reachable vulnerabilities lowers the likelihood of a successful, broad-scale compromise from "Almost Certain" to "Rare."
